Five learners have been killed in a road crash in Hlogotlou outside Grobblersdaal in Limpopo. Police spokesperson Motlafela Mojapelo says the crash happened Tuesday afternoon. He says the learners aged between 15 and 18 hitchhiked from school and the vehicle they were travelling in veered off the road and rolled several times, killing them Police in Hlogotlou outside Grobblersdal have opened a case of culpable homicide. The crash happened along the R574 road between Grobblersdal and Mpudulle.